history.content:
I asked a similar question a little bit ago. The post is now titled EEC106A. People made it clear that the class historically hasn't required it. People I've talked to just recommend I look over the 120 material over the summer and take it concurrently if I'm interested. You could also take it concurrently as well. 120 seems to be a popular prerequisite for many EE classes and if you plan to take more it might be a good investment. 

-----------------------

I talked to Sastry this morning, and he isn't planning to change anything about the prereqs. You should be fine without 120.
